<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/17315286-laurance"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1365650356i/17315286._UY100_CR13,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/17315286-laurance">Laurance</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">This book was written too long ago for me to think that&apos;s likely. I&apos;ve also read before that many characters in this book are loosely based on real li<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">This book was written too long ago for me to think that's likely. I've also read before that many characters in this book are loosely based on real life Atlanta personalities. Charlie does make me think about Trump a lot, but Charlie is a consummate rural southerner, whereas Trump is a product of upperclass Jersey/NY. Their minds may strike me as similar, but they are miles apart in terms of cultural background.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
